Tropical storm Floyd was forecasted to become a hurricane, potentially threatening the Bahamas and the U.S. southeast.
Residents in Anguilla prepared for the storm, while Floridians stocked up on supplies.
NASA planned to close the Kennedy Space Center as a precaution.
Forecasters warned of possible 150 mph winds and a storm surge of up to 20 feet.
FEMA positioned emergency supplies in Atlanta for quick deployment.
Evacuations were ordered in vulnerable coastal areas.
Officials urged individuals to prepare for the worst.
This serious storm was expected to cause catastrophic damage.
